events.name: New York Knicks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 32 points and Julius Randle added 26 to lead the New York Knicks past the Oklahoma City Thunder 119-97 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks cruise past Thunder 119-97 after shaky start

headlines.description: — James Harden scored 12 of his 24 points in the fourth quarter and had his ninth triple-double with the Nets to help Brooklyn beat the Detroit Pistons 100-95 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden has triple-double, carries Nets over Pistons 100-95

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 23 points and nine rebounds, and Charlotte defeated the short-handed Toronto Raptors 114-104 Saturday night in the Hornets' first game with the general public allowed to attend.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball leads Hornets past short-handed Raptors 114-104

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 33 points, 11 assists and 11 rebounds for his sixth triple-double of the season to help the Milwaukee Bucks to a 125-119 victory over the short-handed Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo triple double helps Bucks beat Wizards 125-119

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 17 of 28 points in the third quarter, Clint Capela had 18 of his 24 in the first half, and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Sacramento Kings 121-106 on Saturday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Capela propel Hawks past Kings 121-106

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Carmelo Anthony scored 26 points and Damian Lillard added 25 points and 10 assists as the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 125-121 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony, Lillard lift Blazers over Timberwolves 125-121

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 21 points and 12 assists, and Kristaps Porzingis scored 25 points to lead the Dallas Mavericks to a 116-103 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic has 21 points, 12 assists, Mavs beat Nuggets 116-103

headlines.description: — Malcolm Brogden scored 25 points and Domantas Sabonis had a triple-double with 22 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists to lead the Indiana Pacers over the Phoenix Suns 122-111 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis' triple-double helps Pacers cool off Suns, 122-111
